title: Grateful Dead Live at Greek Theatre, U. Of California on 1987-06-21
description:
Set 1

Alabama Getaway, Promised Land, West L.A. Fadeaway, Walkin' Blues, Far From Me, Cumberland Blues, Mexicali Blues, Box Of Rain, Don't Ease Me In

Set 2

Women Are Smarter, Crazy Fingers, Saint Of Circumstance, China Doll, Playin' In The Band, Drums, When I Paint My Masterpiece, Black Peter, Throwing Stones, Not Fade Away, E: Brokedown Palace

reviews.review_text: Another great audience recording with weird processing...... The last night of the Berkeley run finds the band in a great semi-experimental mood.  The main result is a 1st set that I actually LIKE -- the "Alabama Getaway > Promised Land > West LA Fadeaway" opener is just great, and sets the tome for the night.  Overall, not as raucous or incendiary as the two nights before, but just a great evening with the band in fantastic form.  But as with the other two AUD shows from this taper, the crowd noise is tracked separate from the songs, and is louder than the songs for some reason.  Not a huge detractor, but a bit sloppy.
